
    Tributes are pouring in for a South African man who died when a hot air balloon crashed in Egypt on Friday. D Jay Wiggill was one of three South Africans who were aboard the hot air balloon, which crashed in Luxor. Another seven tourists were injured, the Department of International Relations and Cooperation (Dirco) confirmed on Friday.  The two other South Africans - both 24-year-old women – were injured, but were said to be in a stable condition, Dirco said.There were 16 people on the sunrise balloon trip. They are from Australia, France, Argentina and Brazil, a statement from the Egyptian embassy in Pretoria said.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuH9B1pxUqvICAduLtCeyt1ph1mg0tvzAWwY-WsrvwW1bcdz50uZIPTgo5Kbp9indpGRBNdsVn0lyYBc7zHTk53P5Bl0JDzZW0vXiQobsjTs6Dnvzo_Wa1lKgm8g5hCZiSViVgj1bzujH4EK64EmJyfXdpaACTszT36npRq_12jU6LX9s1WqhmDA_3IK93RFDpDoXMfX2q-rEuAlsWg9aKl-bBPLntNBfhS3Oln7zeTMTtjLIcx7Z_l7D6dT834iEJNVKYB6tI3JN8K9WhoECfHx6qa0Bo\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzNW-4Ky7WTaSEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
